1
00:02:38,014 --> 00:02:38,984
Gentlemen!

2
00:02:39,008 --> 00:02:39,987
Gentlemen!

3
00:02:40,011 --> 00:02:41,451
In your chairs,
brothers and sisters.

4
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:45,004
Now, I propose that we
devote the closing prayer

5
00:02:45,028 --> 00:02:46,996
to a faithful
member of our flock

6
00:02:47,020 --> 00:02:49,981
who is leaving us
tonight, to fill

7
00:02:50,005 --> 00:02:53,997
a position of great
importance in foreign parts.

8
00:02:54,021 --> 00:02:57,990
I refer to our
brother, Brutus Jones.

9
00:02:59,016 --> 00:03:02,028
Will you bow your
heads in prayer?

10
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:08,991
Almighty everlasting God, we
the people of Hezekiah Baptist

11
00:03:09,015 --> 00:03:13,985
Church is gathered
together for the purpose

12
00:03:14,009 --> 00:03:17,005
of giving into your keeping
our brother, Brutus Jones.

13
00:03:21,007 --> 00:03:25,983
Like the prodigal son in
the story, he's-a setting

14
00:03:26,007 --> 00:03:29,978
out on a far journey.

15
00:03:30,002 --> 00:03:34,998
But this boy ain't
like the prodigal son.

16
00:03:35,022 --> 00:03:40,991
He ain't shiftless,
and he ain't worthless.

17
00:03:41,015 --> 00:03:44,986
Oh, Lord, he ain't puffed up.

18
00:03:45,010 --> 00:03:51,023
And he ain't vainglorious, Lord.

19
00:03:57,007 --> 00:03:57,992
Mm mm, honey.

20
00:03:58,016 --> 00:04:01,999
You sure is wonderful
in them clothes.

21
00:04:02,023 --> 00:04:03,002
Yeah.

22
00:04:03,026 --> 00:04:04,980
I suppose these
clothes is something

23
00:04:05,004 --> 00:04:06,983
to look at back here, honey.

24
00:04:07,007 --> 00:04:09,982
Where I been while I've
been training for the job,

25
00:04:10,006 --> 00:04:11,982
you would notice 'em.

26
00:04:12,006 --> 00:04:15,003
Well, you ought to see them
New York girls on Lenox Avenue.

27
00:04:15,027 --> 00:04:17,978
Them gals is fast, I bet.

28
00:04:18,002 --> 00:04:19,983
Switching theirselves
to catch the men.

29
00:04:20,007 --> 00:04:21,988
But honey, you wouldn't
look at none of them

30
00:04:22,012 --> 00:04:26,999
fast gals whiles you away
from home, would you?

31
00:04:27,023 --> 00:04:28,004
They ain't none of 'em as pretty

32
00:04:28,028 --> 00:04:31,984
in the face like mine gal.

33
00:04:32,008 --> 00:04:34,989
And that prodigal son, he takes

34
00:04:35,013 --> 00:04:37,995
the inheritance for
his pappy gives him,

35
00:04:38,019 --> 00:04:40,978
and he spend it
on the fast life.

36
00:04:41,002 --> 00:04:43,005
But not this boy, Lord.

37
00:04:43,029 --> 00:04:45,985
No, Jesus, not this boy.

38
00:04:46,009 --> 00:04:48,983
And the prodigal son is a liar,

39
00:04:49,007 --> 00:04:51,004
and the truth ain't in him!

40
00:04:51,028 --> 00:04:53,979
But not this boy, Lord.

41
00:04:54,003 --> 00:04:54,999
He got the truth, Lord!

42
00:04:55,023 --> 00:04:56,996
You know I looks up, and there's

43
00:04:57,020 --> 00:05:00,991
the Capitol building, looking
like a palace on the hill.

44
00:05:01,015 --> 00:05:04,980
And the big front door opens,
and the President of the United

45
00:05:05,004 --> 00:05:07,996
States marches down the
avenue with a band before

46
00:05:08,020 --> 00:05:10,005
and a band behind.

47
00:05:10,029 --> 00:05:12,996
And he comes right up to my car,
and he says, just as natural,

48
00:05:13,020 --> 00:05:15,997
"Well, Brutus, you
sure is much of a man.

49
00:05:16,021 --> 00:05:17,986
And I, for one,
wants to compliment

50
00:05:18,010 --> 00:05:18,999
you on landing a job."

51
00:05:21,008 --> 00:05:23,990
Honey, they're singing the
closing song at the church.

52
00:05:24,014 --> 00:05:25,005
We's got time.

53
00:05:25,029 --> 00:05:28,982
Jeff's train's going to pick
me up at the water tank.

54
00:05:29,006 --> 00:05:32,029
But you know they's waiting
to see you before you go.

55
00:05:33,001 --> 00:05:35,024
I sure hate to leave my gal.

56
00:06:00,004 --> 00:06:01,164
Would you hold my hat, honey?

57
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:02,991
Hello, Suzanna.

58
00:06:03,015 --> 00:06:04,002
Hello, Brutus.

59
00:06:04,026 --> 00:06:05,992
- Hello, brother.
- How you doing?

60
00:06:06,016 --> 00:06:07,016
Fine, thank you.

61
00:07:14,014 --> 00:07:15,005
There's your train, son.

62
00:07:15,029 --> 00:07:17,001
Goodbye, folks.

63
00:07:17,025 --> 00:07:18,978
Goodbye, brother.

64
00:07:19,002 --> 00:07:19,978
Take care of yourself.

65
00:07:20,002 --> 00:07:21,003
Goodbye!

66
00:07:24,012 --> 00:07:25,012
Goodbye, Mama.

67
00:07:28,025 --> 00:07:30,008
Goodbye,

68
00:07:51,029 --> 00:07:55,004
Here she is.

69
00:07:55,028 --> 00:07:56,002
Come on, Jones.

70
00:07:56,026 --> 00:07:57,004
Here's my buddy.

71
00:07:57,028 --> 00:07:58,004
Honey, this is Jeff.

72
00:07:58,028 --> 00:07:59,981
Hello, sister.

73
00:08:00,005 --> 00:08:00,985
Make tracks, bo, cause
we's riding right now.

74
00:08:01,009 --> 00:08:02,013
Come on. - All right.

75
00:08:06,009 --> 00:08:06,997
But this is too much!

76
00:08:07,021 --> 00:08:08,995
You is coming back, ain't you?

77
00:08:09,019 --> 00:08:10,028
Oh, sure I's coming back.

78
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:11,999
You just get yourself a
new dress with this, honey.

79
00:08:12,023 --> 00:08:12,997
You know, a red one.

80
00:08:13,021 --> 00:08:14,980
That's your style.

81
00:08:15,004 --> 00:08:16,999
And take care of yourself
until I come back, now.

82
00:08:17,023 --> 00:08:18,004
Come on!

83
00:08:18,028 --> 00:08:19,982
All right, old boy.

84
00:08:20,006 --> 00:08:20,995
It's all right, honey.
Take care of yourself.

85
00:08:21,019 --> 00:08:21,990
Don't worry.

86
00:08:22,014 --> 00:08:23,990
I'll be back very soon.

87
00:08:24,014 --> 00:08:25,028
Take care of yourself.

88
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:27,005
Goodbye, honey!

89
00:08:27,029 --> 00:08:28,991
Goodbye

90
00:08:31,026 --> 00:08:33,003
Bye bye, honey!

91
00:08:33,027 --> 00:08:34,027
Bye bye!

92
00:08:44,011 --> 00:08:46,000
Shine 'em, boy.

93
00:08:46,024 --> 00:08:47,991
You done told 'em goodbye now.

94
00:08:48,015 --> 00:08:49,001
You going to stick to it?

95
00:08:49,025 --> 00:08:50,002
Sure, I is.

96
00:08:50,026 --> 00:08:53,982
Cause you big time from this on.

97
00:08:54,006 --> 00:08:54,994
Now, I suppose
you think you know

98
00:08:55,018 --> 00:08:56,001
all there is about this job.

99
00:08:56,025 --> 00:08:57,979
Sure, didn't you
done instruct me?

100
00:08:58,003 --> 00:08:59,981
Oh, just the rudimentary.

101
00:09:00,005 --> 00:09:02,983
Now we's going to take
up the higher education.

102
00:09:03,007 --> 00:09:03,997
Finances.

103
00:09:04,021 --> 00:09:05,001
Yes, brother.

104
00:09:05,025 --> 00:09:06,001
And right here's
where I estimates

105
00:09:06,025 --> 00:09:07,986
the profits for the run.

106
00:09:08,010 --> 00:09:12,978
Now, if you brushes a dime
out of this, you's doing well.

107
00:09:13,002 --> 00:09:17,002
And number three here, boy,
that's good for a half.

108
00:09:17,026 --> 00:09:19,978
What about this one?

109
00:09:20,002 --> 00:09:21,002
Number five.

110
00:09:23,022 --> 00:09:24,993
A whole section.

111
00:09:25,017 --> 00:09:28,990
That's a honeymoon couple.

112
00:09:29,014 --> 00:09:30,003
That's a natural.

113
00:09:30,027 --> 00:09:33,978
If you plays your hand right,
it means the long green.

114
00:09:34,002 --> 00:09:34,983
Big money, eh?

115
00:09:35,007 --> 00:09:36,003
That's what I want
to tell you about.

116
00:09:36,027 --> 00:09:38,980
You know, there's two kind of
women that rides the Pullman.

117
00:09:39,004 --> 00:09:41,994
There's the kind that says,
"Where you been, Porter?"

118
00:09:42,018 --> 00:09:43,994
That don't mean
nothing but a tip.

119
00:09:44,018 --> 00:09:45,989
Then there's the
kind that sings out,

120
00:09:46,013 --> 00:09:47,994
"Hello there, Jack Johnson!"

121
00:09:48,018 --> 00:09:51,984
And boy, that means money.

122
00:09:52,008 --> 00:09:52,990
The long green.

123
00:09:53,014 --> 00:09:53,999
Yeah.

124
00:09:54,023 --> 00:09:56,985
And I'm going to show
you where to spend it.

125
00:10:19,002 --> 00:10:21,004
Everybody, meet my friend
from South Carolina.

126
00:10:21,028 --> 00:10:22,004
Helen, meet Mr. Jones.

127
00:10:22,028 --> 00:10:24,985
Jones, meet Mr. Green.

128
00:10:25,009 --> 00:10:27,000
Gee, that's very strong.

129
00:10:27,024 --> 00:10:28,000
Come here, Marcella.

130
00:10:28,024 --> 00:10:28,998
Meet Mr. Jones.

131
00:10:29,022 --> 00:10:30,979
This is Marcella, Jones.

132
00:10:31,003 --> 00:10:31,985
Hello, big boy.

133
00:10:32,009 --> 00:10:33,990
I got your fish and
rice all ready for ya.

134
00:10:34,014 --> 00:10:35,001
You know, I'm from
South Carolina, myself.

135
00:10:35,025 --> 00:10:36,989
You told me you
was from Georgia.

136
00:10:37,013 --> 00:10:38,002
Told me Lynchburg.

137
00:10:38,026 --> 00:10:39,999
Marcella sure had a busy ma.

138
00:10:40,023 --> 00:10:43,000
She done born her in every
state south of the line.

139
00:10:43,024 --> 00:10:46,999
This is my New York home, bo,
and you'll always find me here.

140
00:10:47,023 --> 00:10:48,999
Oh, Marcella, where's Undine?

141
00:10:49,023 --> 00:10:50,979
I don't know.

142
00:10:51,003 --> 00:10:53,005
She was around here somewhere.

143
00:11:00,010 --> 00:11:02,986
Didn't know I was coming in, eh?

144
00:11:03,010 --> 00:11:06,002
Honeying up to my gal, eh?

145
00:11:08,026 --> 00:11:09,987
Take it easy.

146
00:11:10,011 --> 00:11:10,988
Don't do that.

147
00:11:11,012 --> 00:11:11,985
Don't do that, son.

148
00:11:12,009 --> 00:11:12,985
Not inside of my house.

149
00:11:13,009 --> 00:11:14,986
You ain't gonna send me to jail.

150
00:11:15,010 --> 00:11:15,982
Uh uh.

151
00:11:16,006 --> 00:11:18,029
Y'all go ahead and dance!

152
00:11:27,016 --> 00:11:29,028
There she is.

153
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:32,010
Undine, meet Mr. Jones.

154
00:11:37,015 --> 00:11:39,996
Pleased to meet you, Mr. Jones.

155
00:11:40,020 --> 00:11:40,992
Wanna dance?

156
00:11:41,016 --> 00:11:41,988
Sure.

157
00:11:42,012 --> 00:11:43,029
Go ahead.

158
00:11:44,001 --> 00:11:46,008
You're my buddy, ain't ya?

159
00:11:57,027 --> 00:11:59,984
How you like the city, big boy?

160
00:12:00,008 --> 00:12:03,001
I like it fine now.

161
00:12:03,025 --> 00:12:04,993
Coming back soon?

162
00:12:05,017 --> 00:12:07,998
Soon as the train'll bring me.

163
00:12:08,022 --> 00:12:10,982
I'll be here.

164
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,990
Honey, I sure glad to see you.

165
00:13:04,014 --> 00:13:06,993
I get to missing you more and
more during these long runs.

166
00:13:07,017 --> 00:13:09,979
You know, you oughtn't ask
me to come here to meet you.

167
00:13:10,003 --> 00:13:10,999
I been afraid.

168
00:13:11,023 --> 00:13:12,979
Afraid a what?

169
00:13:13,003 --> 00:13:13,980
Um, you know.

170
00:13:14,004 --> 00:13:14,028
Jeff.

171
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:16,991
He's a bad actor over me.

172
00:13:17,015 --> 00:13:18,990
Well, you ain't got
nothing to be afraid of.

173
00:13:19,014 --> 00:13:22,986
I can handle that
little two-bits porter.

174
00:13:23,010 --> 00:13:25,979
You oughta throw
him over, anyhow.

175
00:13:26,003 --> 00:13:27,995
Then it'll be just you and me.

176
00:13:28,019 --> 00:13:29,980
Sometimes I wonders.

177
00:13:30,004 --> 00:13:31,029
Wonders what?

178
00:13:32,001 --> 00:13:33,994
If we gonna last.

179
00:13:34,018 --> 00:13:36,985
You ain't got nothing
to worry about, honey.

180
00:13:37,009 --> 00:13:37,999
But you ain't heard
the good news yet.

181
00:13:38,023 --> 00:13:41,004
I been transferred to the
president's private car.

182
00:13:41,028 --> 00:13:43,000
Aw, that ain't nothin'.

183
00:13:43,024 --> 00:13:45,979
Why, Jeff said you don't
make no tips on that job.

184
00:13:46,003 --> 00:13:47,000
That's why he didn't take it.

185
00:13:47,024 --> 00:13:48,028
There you are.

186
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:49,987
That's the difference
between me and Jeff.

187
00:13:50,011 --> 00:13:51,991
He can't see no
bigger than two bits.

188
00:13:52,015 --> 00:13:53,028
Me?

189
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:56,981
Why, I just be steppin' to my
own class on that private car.

190
00:14:04,026 --> 00:14:07,005
Harrington, if
there is no leak,

191
00:14:07,029 --> 00:14:08,992
we stand to clean up millions.

192
00:14:09,016 --> 00:14:09,996
That's the idea.

193
00:14:10,020 --> 00:14:10,991
Good night.

194
00:14:11,015 --> 00:14:11,985
Good night.

195
00:14:12,009 --> 00:14:12,985
Good night, Jones.

196
00:14:13,009 --> 00:14:14,014
Good night, sir.

197
00:14:21,002 --> 00:14:22,005
Anything on your mind, Jones?

198
00:14:22,029 --> 00:14:25,988
I's awful worried
about that merger.

199
00:14:26,012 --> 00:14:29,993
Sure would be bad for
us if that news got out.

200
00:14:30,017 --> 00:14:31,029
Us?

201
00:14:32,001 --> 00:14:33,987
Hm.

202
00:14:34,011 --> 00:14:35,981
How long have you
been with me, Jones?

203
00:14:36,005 --> 00:14:36,993
Six weeks, sir.

204
00:14:37,017 --> 00:14:38,992
Learning fast Jones.

205
00:14:39,016 --> 00:14:42,978
Almost too fast.

206
00:14:43,002 --> 00:14:44,028
Got any money, Jones?

207
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,981
I got about $300 in the bank.

208
00:14:47,005 --> 00:14:47,984
All right.

209
00:14:48,008 --> 00:14:49,987
You're in the pool for $300.

210
00:14:50,011 --> 00:14:51,981
Thank you, sir.

211
00:14:52,005 --> 00:14:54,984
And Jones, I would
rather you didn't

212
00:14:55,008 --> 00:14:57,004
leave the car until Sunday.

213
00:14:57,028 --> 00:14:58,989
Two days solitary.

214
00:14:59,013 --> 00:15:01,995
But it'll be worth it, right?

215
00:15:02,019 --> 00:15:03,984
Yes, sir.

216
00:15:04,008 --> 00:15:05,993
And Jones, when we
get back to New York,

217
00:15:06,017 --> 00:15:09,999
it might be a good idea for
you to go back on your old run.

218
00:15:10,023 --> 00:15:14,982
There's more room for
big men in Georgia.

219
00:15:15,006 --> 00:15:16,006
Yes, sir.

220
00:15:18,016 --> 00:15:21,029
Boy, you sure was born
to wear that oyster front.

221
00:15:22,001 --> 00:15:23,982
Where'd you get such a good fit?

222
00:15:24,006 --> 00:15:25,005
Well, the boss
and me talk it over.

223
00:15:25,029 --> 00:15:27,982
And he sent me to his tailor.

224
00:15:28,006 --> 00:15:30,000
He said, Jones, you got a
position to live up to now.

225
00:15:30,024 --> 00:15:33,004
And you can't afford to be
careless in your attire.

226
00:15:33,028 --> 00:15:35,994
You and Mr. Harrington
must be getting mighty thick.

227
00:15:36,018 --> 00:15:37,986
Well, we just pulled off
a little deal together.

228
00:15:38,010 --> 00:15:39,981
I gave him some valuable advice.

229
00:15:40,005 --> 00:15:42,978
And he said, Jones,
you're learning fast.

230
00:15:43,002 --> 00:15:43,981
You're getting big.

231
00:15:44,005 --> 00:15:45,994
Then he takes me
into partnership.

232
00:15:46,018 --> 00:15:47,988
But ain't you going back
on the Pullman no more?

233
00:15:48,012 --> 00:15:49,999
Oh, I'll stick by the
job for a few more runs.

234
00:15:50,023 --> 00:15:51,998
But things don't seem
to be going quite

235
00:15:52,022 --> 00:15:53,980
right on that old run of mine.

236
00:15:54,004 --> 00:15:54,998
And the boss asked me
to drop down that way,

237
00:15:55,022 --> 00:15:56,005
straighten them out.

238
00:15:56,029 --> 00:15:58,005
Well, I guess since
you'll be down that way,

239
00:15:58,029 --> 00:16:00,995
you'll probably drop
in the White House.

240
00:16:01,019 --> 00:16:02,019
Well, that's an idea.

241
00:16:04,029 --> 00:16:05,985
Look here, what are
you trying to do?

242
00:16:06,009 --> 00:16:07,027
Kid me? - Me?

243
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:08,000
Kid you?

244
00:16:08,024 --> 00:16:09,986
Boy, you're a scream.

245
00:16:10,010 --> 00:16:11,979
"Jones.

246
00:16:12,003 --> 00:16:12,980
You're gettin' big.

247
00:16:13,004 --> 00:16:13,981
You're learnin' fast.

248
00:16:14,005 --> 00:16:16,004
Then he takes me
into partnership."

249
00:16:16,028 --> 00:16:17,981
Come clean, big boy.

250
00:16:18,005 --> 00:16:19,994
Where'd you get that
money, in a crap game?

251
00:16:20,018 --> 00:16:21,005
Go laugh some more.

252
00:16:21,029 --> 00:16:23,028
You done laughed yourself
right off of my payroll.

253
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,994
Oh, honey, sweetheart,
I didn't mean it.

254
00:16:26,018 --> 00:16:27,989
I was only kidding.

255
00:16:28,013 --> 00:16:29,981
No, you's too
funny to live with.

256
00:16:30,005 --> 00:16:31,982
Any woman's baggage what
gets heavier and heavier

257
00:16:32,006 --> 00:16:32,992
the longer you totes 'em.

258
00:16:33,016 --> 00:16:36,981
You got to change 'em
to keep traveling light.

259
00:16:37,005 --> 00:16:38,982
Here's $40, and goodbye.

260
00:16:39,006 --> 00:16:40,982
So you was all set to do
this before you come in, eh?

261
00:16:41,006 --> 00:16:41,028
Through is through.

262
00:16:42,001 --> 00:16:42,985
You heard me.

263
00:16:43,009 --> 00:16:44,982
And you can go back to Jeff.

264
00:16:45,006 --> 00:16:47,002
He still thinks there ain't
