00:51:39,018 --> 00:51:42,982
Oh, it's you, Mr. Smithers.

800
00:51:43,006 --> 00:51:44,989
What news you got to tell me?

801
00:51:45,013 --> 00:51:45,998
Where's all your court?

802
00:51:46,022 --> 00:51:48,003
The generals and the
cabinet ministers and all?

803
00:51:48,027 --> 00:51:52,003
Oh, they mostly run the minute
I closes my eyes... drinking

804
00:51:52,027 --> 00:51:55,978
rum, talking big down the town.

805
00:51:56,002 --> 00:51:56,985
How come you don't know that?

806
00:51:57,009 --> 00:51:58,989
Ain't you sousing with
'em most every day?

807
00:51:59,013 --> 00:52:00,990
Well, I got you in
my business and I...

808
00:52:01,014 --> 00:52:01,999
Your business.

809
00:52:02,023 --> 00:52:04,003
Blimey, when you
landed here, you didn't

810
00:52:04,027 --> 00:52:05,998
have no high and mighty airs.

811
00:52:06,022 --> 00:52:08,005
Talk polite, white man.

812
00:52:08,029 --> 00:52:12,003
Talk polite, do you hear me?

813
00:52:12,027 --> 00:52:14,000
I'm boss here now.

814
00:52:14,024 --> 00:52:14,995
Is you forgotten?

815
00:52:15,019 --> 00:52:15,999
It's all right.

816
00:52:16,023 --> 00:52:17,987
No harm meant, old sop.

817
00:52:18,011 --> 00:52:21,995
Well, I accept your apology.

818
00:52:22,019 --> 00:52:25,997
What I was then is one thing,
and what I is now is another.

819
00:52:26,021 --> 00:52:27,991
I wasn't afraid to hire
you that time after you

820
00:52:28,015 --> 00:52:29,979
broke jail in the States.

821
00:52:30,003 --> 00:52:31,999
No, you didn't have no excuse
to look down on me for that.

822
00:52:32,023 --> 00:52:34,996
You been in jail
yourself more 'n worse.

823
00:52:35,020 --> 00:52:37,004
That's a lie!

824
00:52:40,000 --> 00:52:41,995
Who told you that fairy story?

825
00:52:42,019 --> 00:52:45,004
There's some things
I ain't got to be told.

826
00:52:45,028 --> 00:52:47,989
I can see 'em in folks' eyes.

827
00:52:48,013 --> 00:52:51,981
Well, from what I've been
told, it ain't safe for a black

828
00:52:52,005 --> 00:52:55,005
to kill a white
man in the States.

829
00:52:55,029 --> 00:52:58,978
You mean lynchings scare me?

830
00:52:59,002 --> 00:53:00,983
Well, I'll tell you, Smithers.

831
00:53:01,007 --> 00:53:03,987
Maybe I does kill one
white man back there.

832
00:53:04,011 --> 00:53:05,992
Maybe I does.

833
00:53:06,016 --> 00:53:08,987
And maybe I kills
another right here before

834
00:53:09,011 --> 00:53:09,998
long if he don't look out.

835
00:53:10,022 --> 00:53:11,983
Here, you think
I'd peach on you?

836
00:53:12,007 --> 00:53:12,981
Not me.

837
00:53:13,005 --> 00:53:13,982
I'm your friend, ain't I?

838
00:53:14,006 --> 00:53:15,988
Sure you is.

839
00:53:16,012 --> 00:53:18,004
And you'd better be.

840
00:53:23,012 --> 00:53:25,001
And to show you
that I'm your friend,

841
00:53:25,025 --> 00:53:28,986
I'll tell you that bit
of news I was going to.

842
00:53:29,010 --> 00:53:29,984
Go ahead.

843
00:53:30,008 --> 00:53:30,997
Shoot the breeze.

844
00:53:31,021 --> 00:53:33,993
Must be mighty bad news
from the happy way you look.

845
00:53:34,017 --> 00:53:35,988
Ain't noticed
any of the servants

846
00:53:36,012 --> 00:53:39,005
or the guards around the
place this morning, I ain't.

847
00:53:46,012 --> 00:53:46,993
Oh, they all out in the garden,

848
00:53:47,017 --> 00:53:48,981
sleeping under the trees.

849
00:53:49,005 --> 00:53:51,002
All I gotta do is to ring that
gong and they come flying.

850
00:53:51,026 --> 00:53:52,979
All right.

851
00:53:53,003 --> 00:53:57,005
Ring it now, and
you'll see what I mean.

852
00:53:57,029 --> 00:53:59,012
Sure, I'll ring.

853
00:54:34,028 --> 00:54:37,984
The rotten ship is sinking,
and the bloomin' rats

854
00:54:38,008 --> 00:54:38,994
have slung their hooks.

855
00:54:39,018 --> 00:54:41,009
Low-flung woods niggers.

856
00:54:47,007 --> 00:54:50,983
Well, I reckon overplayed
my hand this once.

857
00:54:51,007 --> 00:54:55,005
A man can't take the pot on
a bobtail flush all the time.

858
00:54:55,029 --> 00:54:58,988
Was I saying I'd sit
in six months more?

859
00:54:59,012 --> 00:55:00,995
Well, I's changed my mind, then.

860
00:55:01,019 --> 00:55:05,979
I cashes in and resign the job
of emperor right this minute.

861
00:55:06,003 --> 00:55:07,996
Well, blimey you're a
cool bird and no mistake.

862
00:55:08,020 --> 00:55:08,999
No use fussing.

863
00:55:09,023 --> 00:55:10,999
When I know the
game's up, I kisses it

864
00:55:11,023 --> 00:55:14,984
goodbye without no long wait.

865
00:55:15,008 --> 00:55:16,980
They's all run off to
the hills, ain't they?

866
00:55:17,004 --> 00:55:17,985
Yes.

867
00:55:18,009 --> 00:55:18,992
Lem was taking 'em,
every man jack of 'em.

868
00:55:19,016 --> 00:55:20,999
Then the revolution
is at the post.

869
00:55:21,023 --> 00:55:23,980
And the emperor better get his
feet smoking up that trail.

870
00:55:24,004 --> 00:55:25,564
Going to look for
your horse, ain't you?

871
00:55:26,001 --> 00:55:26,982
Well, you won't find it.

872
00:55:27,006 --> 00:55:28,366
They steals the
horses first thing.

873
00:55:31,016 --> 00:55:35,979
Well, then I hoofs it.

874
00:55:36,003 --> 00:55:38,006
Feet, do your duty.

875
00:55:41,027 --> 00:55:42,985
3:30.

876
00:55:43,009 --> 00:55:45,995
Sundown's at 6:30 or thereabout.

877
00:55:46,019 --> 00:55:47,996
Ho, I got plenty of
time, make it easy.

878
00:55:48,020 --> 00:55:50,978
Yeah, well don't you
be so blasted sure.

879
00:55:51,002 --> 00:55:53,242
You'll have to hustle to get
to to that port in 12 hours,

880
00:55:54,000 --> 00:55:55,005
even if you knew the trails
like bloomin' native.

881
00:55:55,029 --> 00:55:59,992
Looka here, white man, did you
think I's a natural born fool?

882
00:56:00,016 --> 00:56:01,980
Why, I's gone out in that
forest so many times,

883
00:56:02,004 --> 00:56:04,986
pretending to hunt, I know's
it high and low like a book.

884
00:56:05,010 --> 00:56:07,001
I could find them trails
with my eyes shut.

885
00:56:07,025 --> 00:56:10,981
And I got tin grub hid there
under a big white stone

886
00:56:11,005 --> 00:56:11,998
where I can find it.

887
00:56:12,022 --> 00:56:14,993
Oh, I'll be at the edge of the
forest by the time dark comes.

888
00:56:15,017 --> 00:56:17,994
Once in them woods, them
niggers will never find me.

889
00:56:18,018 --> 00:56:20,988
Dawn tomorrow I reaches
the coast and boards

890
00:56:21,012 --> 00:56:22,988
that French gun boat.

891
00:56:23,012 --> 00:56:25,992
I got to laugh at these fool
black trash around here.

892
00:56:26,016 --> 00:56:27,002
It's so easy.

893
00:56:27,026 --> 00:56:30,993
Supposing something happens
and they does nab you?

894
00:56:31,017 --> 00:56:33,987
I's got five lead bullets
in this gun, good enough

895
00:56:34,011 --> 00:56:35,028
for common bush niggers.

896
00:56:36,000 --> 00:56:37,986
And after that, I's got
this silver bullet left

897
00:56:38,010 --> 00:56:39,998
to cheat 'em outta getting me.

898
00:56:40,022 --> 00:56:43,990
I tells 'em when the time
comes, I kills myself with it.

899
00:56:44,014 --> 00:56:45,983
That's because I'm the
only man in the world

900
00:56:46,007 --> 00:56:47,002
big enough to get me.

901
00:56:47,026 --> 00:56:48,998
Then you had silver bullet made?

902
00:56:49,022 --> 00:56:49,989
Honest?

903
00:56:50,013 --> 00:56:51,029
Oh, I sure did.

904
00:56:52,001 --> 00:56:53,980
Here she be.

905
00:56:54,004 --> 00:56:58,978
Five lead bullets and
a silver baby at last.

906
00:56:59,002 --> 00:57:00,987
Don't she shine pretty?

907
00:57:01,011 --> 00:57:01,994
Let me see.

908
00:57:02,018 --> 00:57:03,004
Keep your hands where
they belong, white man.

909
00:57:03,028 --> 00:57:04,987
Blimey, you'd think
I was a blasted thief.

910
00:57:05,011 --> 00:57:05,993
No, it ain't that.

911
00:57:06,017 --> 00:57:08,978
I know you're scared
to steal from me.

912
00:57:09,002 --> 00:57:11,982
I ain't allowing nobody
to touch this baby.

913
00:57:12,006 --> 00:57:13,992
She's my rabbit's foot.

914
00:57:14,016 --> 00:57:15,992
A sort of charm, eh?

915
00:57:16,016 --> 00:57:19,984
Blimey, you'll need all your
bloomin' charms before long,

916
00:57:20,008 --> 00:57:21,978
so help me.

917
00:57:38,017 --> 00:57:39,988
What's that drumbeating for?

918
00:57:40,012 --> 00:57:41,003
For you!

919
00:57:41,027 --> 00:57:43,991
The blacks is having a
war dance in the hills,

920
00:57:44,015 --> 00:57:46,988
working up their courage
for they start after you.

921
00:57:47,012 --> 00:57:47,984
Let them.

922
00:57:48,008 --> 00:57:49,981
They'll sure need it.

923
00:57:50,005 --> 00:57:52,029
They're making all sorts
of devil spells and charms

924
00:57:53,001 --> 00:57:53,999
against your silver bullet.

925
00:57:54,023 --> 00:57:57,006
Takes more than that
to scare this chicken.

926
00:58:08,013 --> 00:58:10,987
Tonight, when it's
pitch black in the forest,

927
00:58:11,011 --> 00:58:12,004
they'll be sending
their pet devils

928
00:58:12,028 --> 00:58:14,984
and ghosts hounding after you.

929
00:58:15,008 --> 00:58:16,984
You'll find your bloomin'
hair will be standing

930
00:58:17,008 --> 00:58:18,015
on end tomorrow morning.

931
00:58:21,009 --> 00:58:25,986
It's a mighty queer place, that
forest is, even in daylight.

932
00:58:26,010 --> 00:58:28,000
You don't know what
might happen there.

933
00:58:28,024 --> 00:58:31,997
It's that rotten still.

934
00:58:32,021 --> 00:58:35,001
Always sends the cold shivers
down my back the minute

935
00:58:35,025 --> 00:58:36,995
I gets in it.

936
00:58:37,019 --> 00:58:39,005
Go along, white man.

937
00:58:39,029 --> 00:58:41,990
You ain't talking to this baby.

938
00:58:42,014 --> 00:58:44,982
What ghosts and
got to do with me?

939
00:58:45,006 --> 00:58:46,991
Well, don't you know I was
a member in good standing

940
00:58:47,015 --> 00:58:48,983
of the Baptist church?

941
00:58:49,007 --> 00:58:50,000
Let 'em try their
heathen tricks.

942
00:58:50,024 --> 00:58:53,029
And the Baptist church
done protect me.

943
00:58:54,001 --> 00:58:54,990
Land 'em all in hell.

944
00:58:55,014 --> 00:58:56,981
Yeah, you ain't paid
much heed to your Baptist

945
00:58:57,005 --> 00:59:00,029
church down here, taking up with
them bloomin' witch doctors.

946
00:59:01,001 --> 00:59:02,984
Oh, sure, I pretend.

947
00:59:03,008 --> 00:59:05,002
It don't get me nothing
to do missionary work

948
00:59:05,026 --> 00:59:07,004
for the Baptist church.

949
00:59:07,028 --> 00:59:08,989
I's after the coin.

950
00:59:09,013 --> 00:59:13,029
And I lays my religion on
the shelf for the time being.

951
00:59:14,001 --> 00:59:14,981
But I ain't got
the time to waste

952
00:59:15,005 --> 00:59:15,999
no more fool talk with you.

953
00:59:16,023 --> 00:59:18,001
I'm going away this second.

954
00:59:21,025 --> 00:59:22,003
So long, white man.

955
00:59:22,027 --> 00:59:24,001
I'll see you in jail
sometime, maybe.

956
00:59:24,025 --> 00:59:25,983
Not me, you won't.

957
00:59:26,007 --> 00:59:27,978
Here, you ain't going
out this way, are you?

958
00:59:28,002 --> 00:59:30,003
You think I'd sneak out the
back door like a common nigger?

959
00:59:30,027 --> 00:59:31,984
I's emperor yet, ain't I?

960
00:59:32,008 --> 00:59:33,984
And the Emperor Jones
leaves the way he come.

961
00:59:34,008 --> 00:59:36,000
And that black trash
don't dare stop him.

962
00:59:36,024 --> 00:59:37,029
Not yet, leastways.

963
00:59:46,004 --> 00:59:49,998
Listen to that roll
call, will you?

964
00:59:50,022 --> 00:59:53,019
Must be a mighty big
drum carry that far.

965
00:59:56,006 --> 00:59:59,980
Well, if they ain't no whole
brass band to see me off,

966
01:00:00,004 --> 01:00:02,995
I sure got the drum part of it.

967
01:00:03,019 --> 01:00:05,012
So long, white man.

968
01:00:13,024 --> 01:00:16,020
Give my regards to
any ghosts you meet.

969
01:00:33,018 --> 01:00:34,005
Here I is.

970
01:00:34,029 --> 01:00:37,985
In the nick of time, too.

971
01:00:38,009 --> 01:00:43,028
Sure, I's
tuckered out, sure enough.

972
01:00:44,000 --> 01:00:44,984
Whew.

973
01:00:45,008 --> 01:00:47,000
That soft emperor job
sure ain't no training

974
01:00:47,024 --> 01:00:49,986
for a long hike over that
plain in the broiling sun.

975
01:00:55,005 --> 01:00:56,992
Bush niggers.

976
01:00:57,016 --> 01:01:01,000
A wonder they wouldn't get
sick of beating that drum.

977
01:01:01,024 --> 01:01:04,989
Sound louder, seem like.

978
01:01:05,013 --> 01:01:07,979
When did they start in after me?

979
01:01:08,003 --> 01:01:11,005
Oh, sure, they miles
and miles behind.

980
01:01:11,029 --> 01:01:14,001
What you getting fidgety about?

981
01:01:14,025 --> 01:01:15,980
You know what?

982
01:01:16,004 --> 01:01:16,982
Your belly's empty.

983
01:01:17,006 --> 01:01:17,997
That's what's the
matter with you.

984
01:01:18,021 --> 01:01:19,997
Nothing but wind
on your stomach.

985
01:01:20,021 --> 01:01:21,993
Course you feels diggety.

986
01:01:22,017 --> 01:01:26,981
Well, we eats
right here and now.

987
01:01:27,005 --> 01:01:28,981
White stone, white stone.

988
01:01:29,005 --> 01:01:30,992
Where is you?

989
01:01:31,016 --> 01:01:32,995
Ah, here you is.

990
01:01:33,019 --> 01:01:34,996
I know this was the right place.

991
01:01:35,020 --> 01:01:39,978
Box of grub, come to me.

992
01:01:40,002 --> 01:01:42,986
Ain't here.

993
01:01:43,010 --> 01:01:45,982
Has I lost the place?

994
01:01:46,006 --> 01:01:47,998
There's another stone.

995
01:01:48,022 --> 01:01:49,022
Yes, that's it.

996
01:01:53,005 --> 01:01:54,986
Ain't here, neither.

997
01:01:55,010 --> 01:01:56,001
Grub, where is you?

998
01:01:56,025 --> 01:01:57,988
You ain't here.

999
01:01:58,012 --> 01:02:01,013
Has I got to go hungry
in them woods all night?

1000
01:02:05,007 --> 01:02:09,003
Can't tell nothing
from them trees.

1001
01:02:09,027 --> 01:02:13,029
Nothing around here look
like I ever seen it before.

1002
01:02:14,001 --> 01:02:16,997
I done lost the
place sure enough.

1003
01:02:17,021 --> 01:02:19,978
Mighty queer.

1004
01:02:20,002 --> 01:02:21,002
Mighty queer.

1005
01:02:24,002 --> 01:02:27,001
Woods, is you trying to
put something over on me?

1006
01:02:30,002 --> 01:02:30,983
Who that? Who that?

1007
01:02:31,007 --> 01:02:31,988
What is you?

1008
01:02:32,012 --> 01:02:40,012
Get away from me before
I... They're gone.

1009
01:02:41,018 --> 01:02:44,987
Yeah, that shot fix 'em.

1010
01:02:45,011 --> 01:02:46,989
Oh, it was only a little animal.

1011
01:02:47,013 --> 01:02:48,990
Little wild pigs, I reckon.

1012
01:02:49,014 --> 01:02:53,979
They maybe rooted out
your grub and eat it.

1013
01:02:54,003 --> 01:02:54,993
Sure, you fool nigger.

1014
01:02:55,017 --> 01:02:58,001
What you think they is, hants?

1015
01:03:04,012 --> 01:03:06,994
You give the game away
when you fired that shot.

1016
01:03:07,018 --> 01:03:09,025
Them niggers'll hear
that for certain.

1017
01:03:17,004 --> 01:03:17,983
Get in, nigger.

1018
01:03:18,007 --> 01:03:18,988
What you scared at?

1019
01:03:19,012 --> 01:03:20,990
Ain't nothing there
but the trees.

1020
01:03:21,014 --> 01:03:22,028
Get in there.

1021
01:03:35,001 --> 01:03:35,990
The moon's rising.

1022
01:03:36,014 --> 01:03:38,981
Did you hear that, nigger?

1023
01:03:39,005 --> 01:03:42,999
Get more light from this out,
and you sees where you's going.

1024
01:03:43,023 --> 01:03:43,996
Cheer up.

1025
01:03:44,020 --> 01:03:47,010
From now on you has a snap.

1026
01:03:51,009 --> 01:03:51,999
Whew.

1027
01:03:52,023 --> 01:03:54,992
It's warm.

1028
01:03:55,016 --> 01:03:58,002
And that's a fact.

1029
01:03:58,026 --> 01:04:03,980
How long I been making
tracks in these here woods?

1030
01:04:04,004 --> 01:04:05,019
Feel like forever.

1031
01:04:08,026 --> 01:04:13,011
This am a long night
for you, your majesty.

1032
01:04:16,006 --> 01:04:17,003
Majesty.

1033
01:04:17,027 --> 01:04:20,997
There ain't much majesty
about this baby now.

1034
01:04:21,021 --> 01:04:21,995
Never mind.

1035
01:04:22,019 --> 01:04:23,988
It's all a part of the game.

1036
01:04:24,012 --> 01:04:26,002
This night come to an
end like everything else.

1037
01:04:26,026 --> 01:04:30,003
You gets there safe and has
that bank roll in your hands,

1038
01:04:30,027 --> 01:04:32,005
then you laughs at all this.

1039
01:05:13,026 --> 01:05:15,992
What you singing
for, you poor nigger?

1040
01:05:16,016 --> 01:05:20,980
Want all the world to hear you?

1041
01:05:21,004 --> 01:05:23,992
Hear that old drum.

1042
01:05:24,016 --> 01:05:27,003
Sure gets nearer from the sound.

1043
01:05:27,027 --> 01:05:31,987
They're packing
it along with 'em.

1044
01:05:32,011 --> 01:05:34,012
Time for me to move.

1045
01:05:38,025 --> 01:05:42,028
What's the little queer,
clickety sound I hear?

1046
01:05:43,000 --> 01:05:46,978
Sound like... sound... it
sounds like some nigger

1047
01:05:47,002 --> 01:05:48,005
were shootin' crap.

1048
01:05:48,029 --> 01:05:52,003
Time I beats it quick
when I get them notes.

1049
01:05:52,027 --> 01:05:53,003
Who there?

1050
01:05:53,027 --> 01:05:55,001
Who that?

1051
01:05:55,025 --> 01:05:57,013
Is that you, Jeff?

